                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">All stuns are hardcapped in code at 5.25 seconds on NPCs, according to EQ devs.
<br />

<br />
They are in the middle of moving this hard code into the spell data.
<br />

<br />
Now, if this is true, then enchanter 8 second stuns have been no better than our 6 second stuns in non-PVP.
<br />

<br />
It is claimed this isn't a recent change
<br />

<br />
At this point, I would advise people to parse and confirm this is true for enchanter spells.  Because if it isn't true right now, it will be true after the next patch.
<br />

<br />
I know how easy it is to stun lock using Slant/Skew/Shift.  I can't believe it is that easy with only a 5.25 second (<span style="font-style: italic">edit</span>) duration time on all 3.
<br />

<br />
With a quarter-second of UI delay, that's a 14.0-14.25 second cycle (Skew determines cycle length) with only 15.75 seconds of total stunning.  That allows for a grand total of .75 seconds of slack overlap in the stun cycle.
<br />

<br />
In the L Flux/Shift/Skew cycle, that's 14.5 seconds of stunning in a 14.0-14.25 second stun cycle -- less than half a second of total stun overlap.
<br />

<br />
Or, in other words, our L 52 stun has the same duration as our L 20 stun.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
