                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I do think we actually do get slightly more than the claimed 5.25 seconds due to some other factor of the game engine not yet taken into account though. Chaining Colour Shift followed by Boltran's (at 2.25 + 4.0 sec, pre-focus items) used to work quite reliably. CC followed by CoD with 15% focus haste only (2.25 + 4.25) was also a feasible technique if you back off a bit during the spell gems' recycling.
<br />

<br />
If I'd had to take a wild guess I'd guess being stunned reset a mob's attack delay as if it had just taken a swing when the attack wore off. I have not tested this.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=308116" target="_blank" class="postlink">Ceranai</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
